Xygenics

	Philosophy

		-
			Xygenics is the act of altering the genetic code and expression of a subject and their
			unborn offspring.

			If the subject is human, their consent is required.
		-

	Principles

		Comparison with Eugenics

			-
				Xygenics is the voluntary removal of bad genes from the gene pool.

				Eugenics is the involuntary removal of people with bad genes from the gene pool.

				Thus xygenics is ethical whereas eugenics is not.
			-